-- Colombia Stocks: EEB, Helm Bank, Pacific Rubiales Were Active
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   L a y a
-- 2012-07-19T20:49:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-19/colombia-stocks-eeb-helm-bank-pacific-rubiales-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 0.4 percent to 13,723.39. The Colcap
Index rose 0.3 percent to 1,671.02.  Empresa de Energia de Bogota SA  (EEB CB), Colombia’s
second-biggest electricity distributor, rose 1.4 percent to
1,050 pesos after jumping as much as 3.4 percent earlier in the
day. The company announced that second-quarter profit doubled
from a year earlier.  Helm Bank SA (PFBHELMB)   rose 1.6 percent to 518 pesos,
extending its two-day rally to 7.5 percent. Diario Financiero
newspaper reported yesterday that Chile’s Corpbanca is in talks
to buy the Colombian lender. Corpbanca declined to answer e-
mailed questions on the report. Helm Bank didn’t respond to a
phone message requesting comment.  Oil advanced to the highest level in eight weeks on growing
concern that instability in the  Middle East  will disrupt
supplies from the region responsible for about 30 percent of
world production.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates the
country’s largest oil field, rose 1.1 percent to 40,660 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Laya in  New York  at 
